						               													<description>&amp;quot;The Battle of Algiers&amp;quot; - Terrorism versus Torture&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has two players. One plays the FLN and the other the paratroopers. The winner is the player who ends the game with the more political points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The map represents Algiers in 1960 (three years after the battle of Algiers)&amp;#10;It is divided into 7 zones, each zone divided into 3 areas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FLN players have 40 counters. Each counter represents a FLN cell with a value. This value is the level of the cell: I for the simplest FLN Activists, II for the FLN Cell Members, III for the FLN Leftenents, IV for the FLN Chiefs and V for the FLN Leaders.&amp;#10;FLN players has 15 level I counters, 12 level II, 7 level III, 5 level IV and one level V.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Para player has 6 counters of different colours, one for each regiment engaged in the Battle of Algiers.&amp;#10;He also has 6 CC counter for the Commandments Centers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
